### DVT Elevator Challenge API - Sample Requests
### Base URL: https://localhost:7xxx or http://localhost:5xxx

@baseUrl = https://localhost:7001
@buildingId = 1
@elevatorId = 1

### ============================================
### BUILDINGS
### ============================================

### Get all buildings
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/buildings
Accept: application/json

### Get building by ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/buildings/{{buildingId}}
Accept: application/json

### Create a new building
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/buildings
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Tech Hub",
  "totalFloors": 25
}

### ============================================
### ELEVATORS
### ============================================

### Get all elevators
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/elevators
Accept: application/json

### Get elevators by building
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/elevators/building/{{buildingId}}
Accept: application/json

### Get elevator by ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/elevators/{{elevatorId}}
Accept: application/json

### Get elevator status
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/elevators/{{elevatorId}}/status
Accept: application/json

### Get all elevator statuses for a building
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/elevators/building/{{buildingId}}/statuses
Accept: application/json

### Create a new elevator
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/elevators
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Elevator D",
  "initialFloor": 0,
  "maxCapacity": 12,
  "speed": 60,
  "elevatorTypeId": 1,
  "buildingId": 1
}

### Set elevator to maintenance mode
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/elevators/{{elevatorId}}/maintenance
Content-Type: application/json

true

### Remove elevator from maintenance mode
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/elevators/{{elevatorId}}/maintenance
Content-Type: application/json

false

### ============================================
### PASSENGER REQUESTS
### ============================================

### Request elevator - Going Up
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/passengerrequests
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "sourceFloor": 0,
  "destinationFloor": 10,
  "passengerCount": 3,
  "buildingId": 1
}

### Request elevator - Going Down
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/passengerrequests
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "sourceFloor": 15,
  "destinationFloor": 2,
  "passengerCount": 5,
  "buildingId": 1
}

### Request elevator - Multiple passengers
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/passengerrequests
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "sourceFloor": 5,
  "destinationFloor": 18,
  "passengerCount": 8,
  "buildingId": 1
}

### Get active requests for a building
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/passengerrequests/building/{{buildingId}}/active
Accept: application/json

### Get request history (paginated)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/passengerrequests/building/{{buildingId}}/history?pageNumber=1&pageSize=20
Accept: application/json

### Get request by ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/passengerrequests/1
Accept: application/json

### ============================================
### FLOORS
### ============================================

### Get all floors for a building
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/floors/building/{{buildingId}}
Accept: application/json

### Get floor status
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/floors/building/{{buildingId}}/floor/5/status
Accept: application/json

### ============================================
### HEALTH CHECK
### ============================================

### Check API health
GET {{baseUrl}}/health
Accept: application/json

### ============================================
### SCENARIO TESTS
### ============================================

### Scenario 1: Rush hour simulation
### Multiple requests from ground floor

POST {{baseUrl}}/api/passengerrequests
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "sourceFloor": 0,
  "destinationFloor": 5,
  "passengerCount": 4,
  "buildingId": 1
}

###

POST {{baseUrl}}/api/passengerrequests
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "sourceFloor": 0,
  "destinationFloor": 12,
  "passengerCount": 6,
  "buildingId": 1
}

###

POST {{baseUrl}}/api/passengerrequests
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "sourceFloor": 0,
  "destinationFloor": 18,
  "passengerCount": 3,
  "buildingId": 1
}

### Scenario 2: Capacity test
### Request with high passenger count

POST {{baseUrl}}/api/passengerrequests
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "sourceFloor": 3,
  "destinationFloor": 15,
  "passengerCount": 15,
  "buildingId": 1
}

### Scenario 3: Opposite directions
### Simultaneous up and down requests

POST {{baseUrl}}/api/passengerrequests
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "sourceFloor": 2,
  "destinationFloor": 19,
  "passengerCount": 4,
  "buildingId": 1
}

###

POST {{baseUrl}}/api/passengerrequests
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "sourceFloor": 18,
  "destinationFloor": 1,
  "passengerCount": 3,
  "buildingId": 1
}

### ============================================
### ERROR SCENARIOS
### ============================================

### Invalid request - Same floor
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/passengerrequests
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "sourceFloor": 5,
  "destinationFloor": 5,
  "passengerCount": 2,
  "buildingId": 1
}

### Invalid request - Negative floor
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/passengerrequests
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "sourceFloor": -1,
  "destinationFloor": 10,
  "passengerCount": 2,
  "buildingId": 1
}

### Invalid request - Zero passengers
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/passengerrequests
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "sourceFloor": 0,
  "destinationFloor": 10,
  "passengerCount": 0,
  "buildingId": 1
}

### Invalid request - Too many passengers
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/passengerrequests
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "sourceFloor": 0,
  "destinationFloor": 10,
  "passengerCount": 100,
  "buildingId": 1
}

### Non-existent building
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/passengerrequests
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "sourceFloor": 0,
  "destinationFloor": 10,
  "passengerCount": 2,
  "buildingId": 999
}

### Non-existent elevator
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/elevators/999
Accept: application/json
